Lunexia on Osu! 10/21/2022 7:08 AM
That's the thing, you don't want to do that too much as it would look scummy. It's hard to do, but finding actual "slips" from non-mafia player and pushing them is something that you can also do. Doing a mix of both is usually what you want to go for. #1 find town members derping, if necessary put it a bit out of context, not too much ofc. Likely people won't backread, or its easy to put it off as a missunderstanding. #2 Fill gaps with other stuff you just say in order to show presence. #3 You can throw in some reads on fellow mafia, but majority should be on town members (for scum reads), you want to misslynch, not sell out your mafia. #4 Try and fill so much of the discussion that you drown out the noise of more silent town members, control it to a degree if possible. Don't ask more silent people for their opinion, ask already top posting townies. -> Keep the silent silent and the loud louder than you, that gives you a reason to be alive later while the loud townies die and the silent misslynchable as you keep them out of discussing content.
